{"timestamp": "2025-12-16 15:04:28.372232", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content=\"You are provided with the following network description and its current state:\\nNetwork Description: An enterprise hierarchical network using FRR OSPF with multiple areas: three core routers form the backbone (area 0) with /31 infrastructure links from 172.16.0.0/16,core1/core2 connect to distribution routers, which in turn bridge to access switches. User hosts are statically addressed in subnets `10.<core>.<dist>.0/24` with their default gateway on the distribution switch and DNS pointed to a central DNS server. A server farm in `10.200.0.0/24` hangs off a dedicated OSPF router (area 0) and hosts one Bind DNS server for the `local` zone plus several Apache web servers published as `web0.local`…`web3.local`, all reachable end-to-end via OSPF.\\nSwitches: switch_access_1_1_1, switch_access_2_1_1\\nHosts: host_1_1_1_1, host_2_1_1_1\\nDns Servers: dns_server\\nWeb Servers: web_server_0, web_server_1, web_server_2, web_server_3\\nRouters (FRRRouting): router_core_1, router_core_2, router_core_3, switch_dist_1_1, switch_dist_2_1, switch_server_access\\nTopology: (router_core_1:eth0, router_core_2:eth0), (router_core_1:eth1, router_core_3:eth0), (router_core_1:eth2, switch_dist_1_1:eth0), (router_core_2:eth1, router_core_3:eth1), (router_core_2:eth2, switch_dist_2_1:eth0), (router_core_3:eth2, switch_server_access:eth5), (switch_access_1_1_1:eth1, host_1_1_1_1:eth0), (switch_access_2_1_1:eth1, host_2_1_1_1:eth0), (switch_dist_1_1:eth1, switch_access_1_1_1:eth0), (switch_dist_2_1:eth1, switch_access_2_1_1:eth0), (dns_server:eth0, switch_server_access:eth0), (web_server_0:eth0, switch_server_access:eth1), (web_server_1:eth0, switch_server_access:eth2), (web_server_2:eth0, switch_server_access:eth3), (web_server_3:eth0, switch_server_access:eth4)\\n\\nYour goal is to analyze the network condition and, if needed, use the available tools.\\nYou need to generate a troubeshooting diagnosis report.\\nThe report should reflect your assessment of the network's health, indicate any abnormal behavior you identify, and describe relevant findings based on your analysis.\\n\\nFocus on producing an informative and coherent diagnostic report derived from the network state.\\nDo not need to propose any solutions or remediation steps at this stage.\" additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='638c666d-2e30-47e4-9717-41fcb43b0f23'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
